<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Dalantia wrote:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Here's a thought...<br>
<br>
Give warriors a mana pool based on their str/agi/dex and allow them to draw on it for an array of techniques, one line of them being an aggro increasing line. Or take it out of their fatigue pool. KEI and other mind buffs, like bards, don't affect this mana pool, it simply regenerates over time. FT also does not affect this pool, but they get their own effect to help bolster it up.<br>
<br>
Just random_thought_01 that popped into my head, though..<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That will never happen Dalantia as it is too complex to add a *new* type of mana into the game. Something that fundamental does not ever change.<br>
<br>
However I appreciate the creativity in your solution. As for the warrior class, I do not think we want mana or anything like it. What we have in the form of advanced techniques are disciplines.<br>
<br>
I believe it is high time to introduce a new discipline at level 63 or 61 called the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Discipline of Hate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (or whatever name you wish) that would be exactly like defensive but for aggro<br>
<br>
- 3 minute duration<br>
- 10 minute reuse<br>
- +30% aggro like the Shadowknight Voice line<br>
- the penalty for this discipline should be a loss of 100 raw atk or some sort of substantial loss in offensive prowess. Perhaps the same code for pathetic hits that triggers when defensive is activated could be used.<br>
<br>
This is balanced in the face of making raids trivial because we must choose between defensive or hate. Additionally this would make warriors more viable in Planar xp groups where we could care less about defensive most of the time but could really use that aggro when we must. <br>
<br>
Hybrids would still maintain supremacy in locking down and giving away taunt whenever they wish to at any point, while warriors would be able to aggro extremely well when the situation calls for it at the cost of offensive power and the realization that disciplines are not always available.<br>
<br>
What do you guys think? I'm not hopeful that SoE is even reading this but if they do, I think this is a resolution that would be satisfactory to all tanking classes. <br>
